  "subject": "5G-core-nf-simulator code",
  "commit_message": "5G-core-nf-simulator code\n\nThe pylint linter reports LOTS of critical errors\nUntil I got some feedback from the developer, I created a pylintrc,\nin order to allow a first merge despite of all the errors.\n\nBut the quality of the code does not match the integration criteria.\nAll the C* and E* errors indicated in the .pylintrc file shall be corrected\nin order to match integration criteria\n\nTopic to be discussed during the Integraiton meeting\n- option 1: we abandon the patch but the repo is empty\n- option 2: we merge with the exceptions\n- option 3: errors fixed then merged\n\nof course 3 is the priviledged option.\nbut if not possible, we need to take a decision\n\nIssue-ID: INT-1843\n\nChange-Id: Ie63ccfaec6be04d47cd12e000d386389e4110a1d\nSigned-off-by: PRAVEEN_SPR <praveen.velugubantla123@gmail.com>\nSigned-off-by: morganrol <morgan.richomme@orange.com>\n",
